WEBVTT

01:24.152 --> 01:27.221
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:27.255 --> 01:29.823
(INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

01:36.830 --> 01:39.700
That wasn't a store robbery.

01:39.733 --> 01:41.802
That was an assassination.

01:41.835 --> 01:45.173
That wasn't a clerk.
That was a wise guy.

01:45.206 --> 01:48.542
How do I know? (CHUCKLES)

01:48.576 --> 01:52.213
I spent a little time with
the FBI's
organized crime unit.

01:52.246 --> 01:54.548
I guess you could say that
I'm intimately knowledgeable

01:54.582 --> 01:56.617
with the seedy and rancorous
workings of the mob

01:56.650 --> 01:59.287
in the Midwest
section of this country.

01:59.320 --> 02:01.422
I know a gangland
slaying when I see one,

02:01.455 --> 02:03.524
and that's exactly
what this baby is.

02:03.557 --> 02:07.361
I'd look into it
myself personally,
but I got a date tonight.

02:07.395 --> 02:10.163
Think I'll take
the private jet out

02:10.198 --> 02:12.800
and fly to Spain,
pick up the little lady.

02:12.833 --> 02:15.636
Do the subsonic tummy
bump at 30,000 feet.

02:15.669 --> 02:18.472
Then glide back into the U.S.
of A. by dawn.

02:18.506 --> 02:23.177
I know what you're gonna say,
"Jim. Jim Dodge, settle down.

02:23.211 --> 02:25.446
"Relax. You owe it to
yourself." (CHUCKLING)

02:25.479 --> 02:27.581
I'll tell you what I
tell everybody else.

02:27.615 --> 02:31.585
Any little Fraulein that
expects anything more from me

02:31.619 --> 02:33.287
than a little bit of pleasure
and a little bit of danger

02:33.321 --> 02:35.489
and a great set of pectorals,

02:35.523 --> 02:37.425
she's looking for
a fall right on her ass.

02:37.725 --> 02:38.926
(YELPS)

02:38.959 --> 02:42.230
(DOGS BARKING)

02:42.263 --> 02:44.232
Hubie, Hubie, Hubie, Hubie!

02:44.265 --> 02:46.234
Get out of here!
Let me tell you something.

02:46.267 --> 02:48.736
If you know
what's good for you,
don't you ever come back!

02:49.570 --> 02:51.038
Wait a minute, now, Hubie.

02:51.071 --> 02:53.674
You're not gonna find someone
who has the relationship
with those animals

02:53.707 --> 02:55.443
that I do.
(BARKING CONTINUES)

02:55.476 --> 02:58.178
Listen to the dogs, Hubie.
They love me!

02:59.680 --> 03:02.783
It all started when I was 15.

03:02.816 --> 03:05.819
That's when I invented
the artificial cow heart.

03:05.853 --> 03:08.556
Oh, that was a big thing.

03:08.589 --> 03:11.792
A little before your time,
but it made all
the newspapers,

03:11.825 --> 03:14.528
ABC, NBC, CBS,
they all picked up on it,

03:14.562 --> 03:17.798
but it's more or less
a hobby for me, boys.

03:18.799 --> 03:21.001
BOY: Scoot over!

03:21.034 --> 03:23.437
(GRUNTS) Actually,

03:24.672 --> 03:28.442
today I decided that I've gone
just about as far I can go

03:28.476 --> 03:30.611
in the animal
health-care business.

03:30.644 --> 03:33.814
But that's your question.
The reason that I'm not
at work this afternoon,

03:33.847 --> 03:38.652
is because I was made an offer
that I simply cannot refuse.
I sold.

03:38.686 --> 03:40.454
Whatcha gonna do
with the cash, Jim?

03:40.488 --> 03:42.423
I don't know. Maybe
I'll invest it overseas.

03:42.456 --> 03:44.458
I've got some projects
in eastern Europe right now.

03:44.492 --> 03:46.294
I don't know. I've got
everything a man needs.

03:46.327 --> 03:49.330
Jim, you just bought
the animal hospital.

03:49.363 --> 03:51.865
How come you sold it so fast?

03:53.534 --> 03:55.969
Tax problem.

03:56.003 --> 03:58.472
And here's my
accountant right now.

03:58.506 --> 04:00.808
Earl, take a bow. (LAUGHS)

04:00.841 --> 04:04.011
20 minutes for lunch, okay?
Go buy another suit.

04:04.044 --> 04:06.347
(LAUGHS) He works for me.

04:06.380 --> 04:08.616
He's scouting some
real estate for me right now.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.018
Yeah,
but the market's real tight.

04:14.021 --> 04:16.423
I like the new uniform,
Lorraine.

04:18.858 --> 04:21.028
You know, with
the right shoes and handbag,

04:21.060 --> 04:23.397
that might be suitable
for a cocktail party.

04:23.897 --> 04:26.434
So... Question.

04:26.467 --> 04:29.803
When in
the world are you going
to start serving sashimi?

04:29.837 --> 04:31.805
Maybe when I
find out what it is.

04:32.973 --> 04:36.744
(CHUCKLES) You've
never heard of sashimi?

04:36.777 --> 04:38.912
You've got to be kidding.

04:38.946 --> 04:42.350
It's this special
Japanese fish you eat raw.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.817
With a little butter sauce,

04:43.851 --> 04:46.887
and you're ready
to go to heaven.

04:46.920 --> 04:51.925
I'd hire you in a minute
if I hadn't already
fired you so many times.

04:51.959 --> 04:54.662
Did you ever
think of leaving town?

04:55.829 --> 04:59.032
Thousands of people
over in St. Louis...

04:59.066 --> 05:02.370
Got no idea how
full of shit you are.

05:04.071 --> 05:07.641
You've been alive for
21 years, my friend.

05:07.675 --> 05:11.812
Plenty of time for most people
to find a place
for themselves.

05:13.414 --> 05:15.916
Well,
I'm not like everybody else.

05:15.949 --> 05:18.586
You know what I'm saying?
(CHUCKLES)

05:18.619 --> 05:20.688
Yeah, that's for sure.

05:23.123 --> 05:25.526
How about if I...

05:25.559 --> 05:27.728
I work for you for free?

05:27.761 --> 05:29.663
(BELL RINGS)

05:29.697 --> 05:32.032
No.

05:32.065 --> 05:34.635
I'm afraid not, Jimmy.

05:35.436 --> 05:37.938
Think about St. Louis.

05:39.607 --> 05:41.008
Hey, Josie.
JOSIE: Hi.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.410
Fill her up?

05:42.443 --> 05:43.577
JOSIE: Fill her up.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.732
How you doin'?

06:18.178 --> 06:19.379
(CHUCKLES)

06:21.615 --> 06:23.451
You got fired again,
didn't you? Didn't you?

06:23.484 --> 06:25.018
Yeah.

06:25.052 --> 06:26.520
(STAMMERING)
Who told you that?

06:26.554 --> 06:28.856
Hubie Marshall
called me at work.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.991
He called you at work?

06:31.024 --> 06:34.862
That's it. Okay,
I'm gonna... I'll speak...
What'd he say?

06:34.895 --> 06:37.731
He said he fired ya!

06:37.765 --> 06:40.033
He said that?
And you believed him?

06:40.067 --> 06:41.502
Damn straight I do!

06:41.535 --> 06:46.874
With all due respect, Dad,
you're Mr. Gullible,
sometimes. (CHUCKLING)

06:46.907 --> 06:49.042
The truth of the matter is,
Dad, I resigned.

06:50.043 --> 06:51.144
I'll tell you
something else, Dad.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.179
Shut up, Jimmy!

06:52.212 --> 06:54.548
When I took the job,
I had no idea

06:54.582 --> 06:57.585
it was gonna be
a hire-fire situation.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.953
Luther Betenhauser's boy
is doing much better.

06:59.987 --> 07:01.188
What's wrong with him?

07:01.221 --> 07:02.623
Fell off his
grandfather's silo.

07:02.656 --> 07:03.891
He's got brain damage.

07:03.924 --> 07:05.092
(MUFFLED) He does not.

07:05.125 --> 07:06.794
He does, too.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.629
Hoover Fey says his
tongue's gonna hang out

07:08.662 --> 07:10.197
the side of his mouth
the rest of his life.

07:10.230 --> 07:12.032
And when he dies
and they bury him,

07:12.065 --> 07:14.502
at the funeral they're
gonna put a mask on him.

07:14.535 --> 07:16.837
Do I have to listen to
this while I'm eating?

07:17.638 --> 07:19.607
Let's talk about
something else.

07:24.945 --> 07:27.080
Josie McClellan
moved to New York.

07:27.114 --> 07:30.050
She did not. I saw her today.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.052
Well,
I don't know how you could.

07:32.085 --> 07:35.022
I heard at the bank
that she got tired
of taking care of her father,

07:35.055 --> 07:36.423
and she told him
to jump in a lake,

07:36.456 --> 07:39.893
and then she left for New York
to get her MBA in
high-fashion design

07:39.927 --> 07:42.630
at the University
of New York City.

07:42.663 --> 07:46.233
I just saw her down
at the gas station
in living color.

07:46.266 --> 07:48.936
We had a cup of java together.

07:48.969 --> 07:53.006
Well,
I'm gonna take Lou Selby's
word over yours any day.

07:53.040 --> 07:56.810
Lou Selby.
Lou Selby's a drunk.

07:56.844 --> 07:59.647
You know, for a guy who's just
lost his umpteenth job,

07:59.680 --> 08:01.615
you sure are handy
with the tongue sword.

08:01.649 --> 08:03.684
You got canned again?

08:03.717 --> 08:05.686
Well, he didn't get canned.

08:06.687 --> 08:07.755
He got fired.

08:09.089 --> 08:10.924
That's gotta be
some kind of a record.

08:12.560 --> 08:13.627
(CLEARS THROAT)

08:15.295 --> 08:17.230
Not only are you
an obnoxious slug,

08:17.264 --> 08:20.067
but you're
a freeloading obnoxious slug.

08:20.100 --> 08:21.969
Well, you should talk.

08:22.002 --> 08:24.137
What are you?
In your mid-forties
and still living at home.

08:25.639 --> 08:28.275
I'm 24, and I pay rent.

08:28.976 --> 08:30.077
JIM: So do I.

08:30.110 --> 08:31.144
You did pay rent.

08:32.011 --> 08:35.582
Dad, you mean
you're cutting my rent?

08:35.616 --> 08:37.650
Hell, no!

08:37.684 --> 08:39.251
You're not paying a rent
'cause you don't have a job

08:39.285 --> 08:40.554
and you don't have any money.

08:40.587 --> 08:43.691
You're out of school
and you live in this house,
you pay rent!

09:03.176 --> 09:05.813
Jim! Yo, Jim!

09:05.846 --> 09:07.848
Jim, wake up!

09:07.881 --> 09:10.017
Hey, get up!

09:12.385 --> 09:14.254
(SCREAMING) Get up!

09:18.859 --> 09:21.929
JIM:
You know, getting this job,

09:21.962 --> 09:24.031
restoring your
faith and pride in me

09:24.064 --> 09:26.099
is a number-one
priority right now, Dad.

09:26.133 --> 09:29.603
Priority ought to be making
something of yourself.

09:29.637 --> 09:31.171
That's right up there.

09:31.204 --> 09:35.342
When I was your age,
I couldn't wait to get
out of my folks' house.

09:37.310 --> 09:38.946
I love living at home.

09:49.723 --> 09:52.993
I don't think this is such
a great place for
me to work, Dad.

09:55.763 --> 09:57.264
Okay,

09:57.297 --> 10:00.600
say I don't get this job,
hypothetically.

10:01.168 --> 10:02.770
Are you gonna be upset?

10:02.803 --> 10:06.073
You don't get this job,
you're on a bus to St. Louis.

10:06.106 --> 10:07.908
St. Louis?

10:07.941 --> 10:10.678
Uncle Jeff's offered
to put you to work
in his garden shop.

10:10.711 --> 10:12.412
I don't know
anything about gardening.

10:12.445 --> 10:14.948
You will learn!

10:14.982 --> 10:18.251
I'm getting
a distinct feeling that
you want me out of your life.

10:18.285 --> 10:21.254
I don't want you
out of my life.
I want you out of my house.

10:23.223 --> 10:24.892
Wow.
Out!

10:24.925 --> 10:26.727
Okay, okay, okay.

10:42.743 --> 10:45.345
MARSH: Are you
sure I can't offer you
a coffee and a bear claw?

10:45.378 --> 10:46.980
JIM: (CHUCKLES) No, thanks.

10:47.014 --> 10:48.782
(LAUGHS) They're very good,
they're fresh.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.383
No, I'm fine.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.219
You don't want one,
and I don't need one.

10:52.252 --> 10:53.954
(BOTH LAUGHING)

10:53.987 --> 10:55.222
Right!

10:55.255 --> 10:56.656
I love the darn things,
though, I tell you.

10:56.690 --> 10:59.292
You know, I got a sweet tooth,
I could eat those
things by the dozen.

10:59.326 --> 11:01.061
By the looks of it, I have.
(LAUGHS)

11:01.094 --> 11:02.763
(LAUGHS) Right.

11:02.796 --> 11:06.299
I tell ya, I'm so excited
that you're considering

11:06.333 --> 11:08.902
joining the Target team.
We all are.

11:10.270 --> 11:11.872
I appreciate that.

11:11.905 --> 11:15.275
Good, then, let's cut
right to the chase, shall we?

11:16.443 --> 11:19.947
We're prepared to
offer you $42,500 a year,

11:19.980 --> 11:22.049
with a full benefit package.

11:22.883 --> 11:24.885
That's dental, medical,

11:24.918 --> 11:26.987
profit sharing, pension,

11:27.020 --> 11:29.857
expense account,
car allowance,

11:29.890 --> 11:31.792
vacation, of course,

11:31.825 --> 11:35.095
and any and all
relocating expenses.

11:35.128 --> 11:39.699
This is our first,
best, and last offer.
What do you think?

11:40.533 --> 11:42.369
Well... (CLEARS THROAT)

11:42.402 --> 11:45.739
C.D., with all due respect,

11:45.773 --> 11:47.307
I came in here

11:47.340 --> 11:50.210
with the number 45
in my mind, and...

11:59.019 --> 12:00.220
(EXHALES)

12:08.095 --> 12:09.196
Hmm.

12:12.365 --> 12:14.968
(CHUCKLING) You've got me.

12:15.002 --> 12:16.036
(CHUCKLING)

12:16.069 --> 12:17.470
45 it is.

12:17.504 --> 12:19.072
(BOTH LAUGHING)

12:19.106 --> 12:20.407
Welcome aboard.

12:20.440 --> 12:21.942
Thank you.

12:21.975 --> 12:23.076
I'd like to buy you lunch.

12:23.110 --> 12:24.211
No, no, no.

12:24.244 --> 12:26.546
Your money's no good here.
Lunch is mine, all right?

12:26.579 --> 12:28.148
I'm not going to
argue with you.

12:28.181 --> 12:29.516
You better not.
I'm bigger than you are.

12:29.549 --> 12:31.118
(BOTH LAUGHING)
(INTERCOM BUZZING)

12:31.151 --> 12:33.086
Hang on a second, will you?
I told her to hold my calls.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.521
Get it.

12:34.554 --> 12:36.123
Yeah, Peg. Uh-huh.

12:37.124 --> 12:39.827
(CHUCKLING) No, it's okay.

12:39.860 --> 12:41.261
No, he's right here
with me now. (LAUGHS)

12:41.294 --> 12:42.863
Hi, Peg. (LAUGHS)

12:42.896 --> 12:45.098
We just closed the deal.
Uh-huh.

12:45.132 --> 12:49.302
Oh, it was a slam-dunk, too.
I got him for 45.

12:49.336 --> 12:51.238
(CHUCKLING)

12:54.441 --> 12:56.276
No, he's right here.

12:57.911 --> 13:00.413
What do you mean,
he missed the plane?

13:03.050 --> 13:05.218
Then who the hell
am I talking to?

13:07.187 --> 13:09.156
(SIGHS) Oh, Lord!

13:10.924 --> 13:14.161
I'll, uh...
I'll get back to you.

13:15.863 --> 13:17.464
Hey, I know a great
little Italian place

13:17.497 --> 13:20.400
that has the best
pasta primatonis in the...

13:20.433 --> 13:22.269
Excuse me a minute,
will you, please?

13:22.302 --> 13:23.837
Lovely wife you have there.

13:23.871 --> 13:25.138
Dodge, James?

13:26.073 --> 13:27.074
Mmm-hmm.

13:28.241 --> 13:29.476
(SIGHS)

13:29.509 --> 13:32.479
James, I'm afraid we have
a little
misunderstanding here.

13:32.512 --> 13:35.215
You see, I thought you
came in for the, uh...

13:35.248 --> 13:38.485
Operations Manager's job.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.054
I have you down here
as night cleanup boy.

13:44.391 --> 13:46.193
Well, I'm a little overpaid

13:46.226 --> 13:49.096
for night cleanup boy,
wouldn't you say, C.D.?
(LAUGHS)

13:50.931 --> 13:54.935
The truth is, James,
I can offer you
$4.44 per hour.

13:58.005 --> 14:01.341
Uh, four, four... $4.44...

14:01.374 --> 14:03.176
$4.44.

14:03.210 --> 14:05.145
What about the benefits?

14:05.178 --> 14:07.447
Two fifteen-minute breaks
and a half hour for lunch.

14:08.982 --> 14:12.619
And the title is,
uh, night cleanup boy?

14:13.453 --> 14:14.621
Yes.

14:17.290 --> 14:19.092
I'll take it.

14:19.126 --> 14:21.194
Oh, and, uh, lose the curl.

14:22.662 --> 14:24.898
Welcome to the Target team.
Thank you.

14:26.499 --> 14:29.903
BOSENBECK: So the parrot says,
"Of course, I can talk.
Can you fly?"

14:29.937 --> 14:32.940
(ALL LAUGHING)

14:34.374 --> 14:38.211
I don't want any damn Japanese
automobile plant in this town.

14:41.114 --> 14:43.083
(STAMMERING) It means jobs.

14:44.251 --> 14:46.186
I don't need a job.

14:46.219 --> 14:49.222
Your governor's tryin' to use
my town as a political chip.

14:49.256 --> 14:50.623
Gentlemen, I resent that.

14:50.657 --> 14:54.928
Well, there could be some
specific benefits
for you personally.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.567
ROGER: Josie!

15:03.436 --> 15:05.405
Yeah?
Come here.

15:05.438 --> 15:08.541
I want you to
meet these gentlemen
from the governor's office.

15:09.742 --> 15:12.012
Come on in here, honey.

15:25.292 --> 15:26.926
(CLEARS THROAT)

15:28.495 --> 15:29.963
Honey, I want you
to meet Bill, uh...

15:29.997 --> 15:31.198
Uh, Bob.

15:32.432 --> 15:34.167
Uh, Bob Bosenbeck.

15:37.504 --> 15:38.571
Bob.

15:52.485 --> 15:54.187
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

15:54.587 --> 15:55.655
Dave.

15:59.026 --> 16:01.228
My pleasure, Dave.

16:01.261 --> 16:03.163
(CHUCKLES)

16:03.196 --> 16:04.964
Right.
Dave Hockner. (CLEARS THROAT)

16:06.333 --> 16:09.169
I don't want to
interrupt your meeting.

16:09.202 --> 16:11.238
Very nice to meet both of you.

16:11.538 --> 16:13.306
Bye.

16:13.340 --> 16:15.042
HOCKNER: Bye.

16:19.746 --> 16:21.548
ROGER: (MUFFLED) Josie?

16:23.116 --> 16:24.517
Josie!

16:25.685 --> 16:27.554
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

16:29.122 --> 16:30.723
(DOOR OPENS)

16:32.225 --> 16:35.395
You pull another
stunt like you did today,

16:35.428 --> 16:38.231
I'll beat the livin'
daylights outta you!

16:50.510 --> 16:52.745
(PASSIONATE MOANING)

16:58.318 --> 16:59.486
(GASPING)

16:59.519 --> 17:00.620
All right, out!

17:01.388 --> 17:04.090
(GIRL SCREAMING)

17:04.124 --> 17:07.727
Out of here, man.
Get out of here!

17:07.760 --> 17:08.828
Get out of the car!

17:08.861 --> 17:10.063
(STRUGGLING)

17:10.530 --> 17:11.798
(GROANS)

17:14.567 --> 17:15.635
(LAUGHS)

17:22.509 --> 17:23.710
(TIRES SCREECHING)

17:24.277 --> 17:26.146
(CAR HONKING)

17:29.549 --> 17:30.683
Right on time!

17:34.254 --> 17:36.123
Everything's going as planned.

17:37.290 --> 17:38.425
You ordered a limousine?

17:39.826 --> 17:42.095
Of course. (CHUCKLES)

17:42.795 --> 17:44.264
My first day at work.

17:44.297 --> 17:47.334
How's it gonna look
if my dad drives me?

17:47.367 --> 17:49.402
A little treat to
myself for getting the job.

17:49.436 --> 17:51.304
It was only 50 bucks.

17:51.838 --> 17:53.740
(WHISTLING)

17:53.773 --> 17:55.208
Right on time, Henry.

17:55.242 --> 17:56.743
Yes, sir.

17:56.776 --> 17:58.545
Henry, the sign... (LAUGHS)

17:58.578 --> 18:00.280
Very well, sir.

18:03.583 --> 18:05.585
Ciao!

18:12.259 --> 18:14.594
Hey, Jim, where are you going?

18:15.562 --> 18:18.165
Hello, boys.

18:18.198 --> 18:20.533
Going to Paris on an F-14.

18:20.567 --> 18:23.436
Got a little peace meeting
with the Vice-President
of Bulgaria.

18:23.470 --> 18:26.306
Business, you know?
Then I'm going to Venice,

18:26.339 --> 18:28.841
for a big spaghetti dinner
with the princess of Austria.

18:28.875 --> 18:31.578
A beautiful lady...
Really big bones.

18:31.611 --> 18:34.414
Remember to brush
your teeth, Melvin!

18:34.447 --> 18:37.584
You, too, Sidney! Adios!

18:39.719 --> 18:42.155
Jim is so cool!

20:08.641 --> 20:09.642
Bobby.

20:11.744 --> 20:13.746
Got a loose tile here.
First thing in the morning,

20:13.780 --> 20:16.316
I want you to take
some epoxy cement
and take care of this.

20:16.349 --> 20:18.418
I don't need a lawsuit, okay?

20:18.451 --> 20:20.820
