22:02.522 --> 22:04.657
You, uh, sweep the aisles,
startin' with
health and beauty,

22:04.691 --> 22:06.559
and you work your way over
to juniors and misses.

22:06.593 --> 22:09.529
Ups and downs, leaving your
debris in the cross aisles.

22:09.562 --> 22:10.663
So I start with
health and beauty...

22:10.697 --> 22:11.731
What did I just say?

22:11.764 --> 22:13.966
I just said to start
with health and beauty, okay?

22:14.000 --> 22:15.668
Then you do your cross aisles.

22:15.702 --> 22:17.537
That'll bring your
dustbin into play.

22:17.570 --> 22:19.772
You take the debris.
You load it into the dustbin.

22:19.806 --> 22:22.675
You take the dustbin out
to the loading dock area

22:22.709 --> 22:24.611
and you empty it
into the receptacle.

22:24.644 --> 22:25.845
You got that? Easy as pie.

22:25.878 --> 22:27.547
Yeah.

22:27.580 --> 22:29.549
Now, I was employed
for a brief period
at Del Taco, and...

22:29.582 --> 22:32.419
I don't care about your
Del Taco experiences, boy.

22:32.452 --> 22:34.821
All right. Now,
we've got this little problem
in this store with grazers.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.656
You know what
a grazer is, boy?

22:36.689 --> 22:38.825
Is that some
sort of farm term?

22:38.858 --> 22:40.660
A grazer is
a customer or an employee

22:40.693 --> 22:42.429
that eats off the shelves,
okay?

22:42.462 --> 22:45.097
Sort of similar
to a cow grazing
in a field of grass.

22:45.131 --> 22:47.800
Only this isn't
a field of grass, okay,
and you're not a cow.

22:47.834 --> 22:50.503
There's no eatin'.
You're not being
paid to eat, so don't!

22:50.537 --> 22:51.871
You got any questions?

22:51.904 --> 22:53.406
Not right offhand, no.

22:53.440 --> 22:54.807
You think you can handle it?

22:54.841 --> 22:56.142
Oh, I'll give it
the old college try.

22:56.175 --> 22:57.810
Don't touch me!

22:58.811 --> 23:01.113
Well,
despite our age difference,

23:01.147 --> 23:02.449
I think I'm really gonna
enjoy working with you.

23:02.482 --> 23:05.017
Let's get
something straight, boy.
You ain't workin' with me.

23:05.051 --> 23:06.986
You're working for me.
(EXCLAIMS)

23:07.019 --> 23:09.722
Still,
I think it's gonna be fun
being around you.

23:09.756 --> 23:10.990
Yeah, I ain't gonna
be anywhere near you.

23:11.023 --> 23:13.793
I'm gonna be home
pumping the pasties
out of Colleen Jackson.

23:13.826 --> 23:15.127
You're not going to be here?

23:15.161 --> 23:16.596
Hell, no.

23:18.130 --> 23:21.834
I'm gonna be here by myself?

23:21.868 --> 23:25.605
Yeah, that's right!
And you'd better stay out
of the ladies' undergoods.

23:27.073 --> 23:30.543
Wait a minute.
Nobody told me
I'd be here alone.

23:30.577 --> 23:31.878
What are you doing?

23:31.911 --> 23:33.179
Saving money.

23:33.212 --> 23:35.147
Wait a minute. Are you
turning off the lights?

23:35.181 --> 23:37.750
In 25 seconds, you got light
in every third aisle.

23:37.784 --> 23:38.951
When the sun
comes up, you turn off

23:38.985 --> 23:39.886
all the lights.
You understand?

23:41.087 --> 23:44.023
No, I don't understand.
Just hold on a second!

23:44.056 --> 23:45.858
I'm locking you in.

23:45.892 --> 23:49.128
When I come back
at 7:00 to open up,
I'll let you out.

23:51.598 --> 23:53.566
You're locking me in?

23:53.600 --> 23:55.034
What do you take
me for, a fool?

23:55.067 --> 23:58.638
Nobody gets a set of keys
on their first night. Nobody!

23:58.671 --> 24:00.607
Now, get to work!

24:01.073 --> 24:02.575
What if there's a fire?

24:02.609 --> 24:03.843
Then the fire
department will come.

24:04.644 --> 24:05.845
