preacher or something!

32:30.482 --> 32:32.151
Come on. Get in the car!

32:34.020 --> 32:35.154
Prick.

32:40.092 --> 32:42.294
Are you sure you
didn't hurt yourself?

32:42.328 --> 32:45.064
Oh, no. Are you kidding?

32:45.097 --> 32:47.499
No, I'm fine. I'm fine.

32:47.533 --> 32:49.035
Can I ask what you were doing?

32:49.068 --> 32:51.037
Uh...
Oh, I was roller-skating.

32:51.770 --> 32:53.472
I know, but why?

32:53.505 --> 32:55.574
Oh, why not?

32:55.607 --> 32:59.311
I got bored. One thing
led to another and...

32:59.345 --> 33:02.414
And I'm roller-skating
in my shorts. (CHUCKLES)

33:02.448 --> 33:04.616
Better question would be,
"What are you doing here?"

33:05.451 --> 33:07.186
Shopping.

33:07.219 --> 33:09.688
Well, we've been
closed for five hours.

33:09.721 --> 33:12.091
Yeah. I fell asleep.

33:12.124 --> 33:13.492
While shopping?

33:13.525 --> 33:15.194
No,
in the ladies' dressing room.

33:15.227 --> 33:18.664
That makes no sense.
You're
a high-profile young ingenue.

33:18.697 --> 33:20.499
I was debating...
What?

33:20.532 --> 33:24.036
Whether or not to get
arrested for shoplifting.

33:24.070 --> 33:27.173
Doesn't your father own, like,
$10 million worth of
real estate in this town?

33:27.206 --> 33:28.807
Well, it's not my fault.

33:28.840 --> 33:30.609
No, no, I didn't imply such.

33:30.642 --> 33:33.812
It just seems funny
that someone of your...

33:33.845 --> 33:35.614
Wealth?

33:35.647 --> 33:37.349
If you will.
Would be shoplifting...

33:37.383 --> 33:39.718
I didn't do it.
I chickened out.

33:40.719 --> 33:43.455
Would consider shoplifting.

33:43.489 --> 33:47.226
It's a long,
dull, self-indulgent,
highly unromantic story

33:47.259 --> 33:49.628
about an overbearing father,

33:49.661 --> 33:51.797
deceased mother and brother

33:51.830 --> 33:55.501
and a completely confused girl
who looks a little like me.

34:07.413 --> 34:08.414
(EXCLAIMS)

34:09.148 --> 34:10.248
(SIGHS)

34:33.371 --> 34:36.175
I sure am glad you dropped by.

34:36.208 --> 34:38.810
I was getting pretty
tired of being with myself.

34:41.880 --> 34:45.684
I guess...
I guess, I'm what you
call a people person.

34:48.853 --> 34:50.222
What are you cooking?

34:50.255 --> 34:51.357
Uh, Hobo Chicken.

34:51.389 --> 34:53.659
It's a glazed
chicken in wine sauce

34:53.692 --> 34:56.594
with vegetables
and skin-on potatoes.

34:56.628 --> 34:58.730
Silverware... Silverware...

35:02.234 --> 35:04.170
It's only 210 calories.

35:04.203 --> 35:06.405
And I don't know
if you're watching

35:06.438 --> 35:08.574
your figure, but I sure am.
(CHUCKLES)

35:08.607 --> 35:10.742
Uh, if you can just
grab a serving spoon

35:10.776 --> 35:12.844
over there,
I think we'll be set.

35:18.317 --> 35:20.419
Uh, keep your
distance from these things.

35:20.452 --> 35:22.588
I think it's safe
to keep five feet.

35:22.621 --> 35:24.122
(BELL DINGS)

35:27.626 --> 35:29.728
I think they're about done.

35:31.897 --> 35:34.366
Well,
dining room's right this way.

35:36.868 --> 35:38.570
Mmm!

35:38.870 --> 35:41.540
Mmm. Oh.

35:41.573 --> 35:45.211
I think my father poured
the cement for your pool.

35:46.612 --> 35:49.548
He's a cement contractor.
Good man.

35:50.716 --> 35:52.318
Bud Dodge?

35:52.351 --> 35:54.953
My mother works at Hoenicker's
over Christmas, part time.

35:54.986 --> 35:56.855
My sister's
a teller at the bank.

35:56.888 --> 35:59.758
My brother's in grade school.
He's not
employed at the moment.

35:59.791 --> 36:02.561
I used to work at
the animal shelter.

36:02.594 --> 36:05.931
But I was terminated.
And now...
Now I'm working here.

36:08.567 --> 36:10.236
Do you always talk this much?

36:12.804 --> 36:15.374
Yeah, I guess I do.

36:15.407 --> 36:17.409
I like talking to people.

36:19.445 --> 36:21.780
I was thinking maybe
you should go into sales.

36:21.813 --> 36:23.181
I've actually tried that.

36:30.556 --> 36:32.824
Some fresh ground pepper?

36:32.858 --> 36:34.360
Please.

36:36.795 --> 36:38.630
Some people don't
like a lot of pepper.

36:38.664 --> 36:40.432
Say when.
That's fine.

36:41.667 --> 36:43.435
I happen to
really like it a lot.

36:43.469 --> 36:46.838
I think it enhances
the natural flavor
of the chicken.

36:50.576 --> 36:53.312
I hope you don't
take this the wrong way.

36:54.045 --> 36:56.315
I've had dreams about you.

36:56.348 --> 36:58.450
You've had dreams about me?

36:59.985 --> 37:01.553
Not recently.

37:01.587 --> 37:03.689
I've had dreams
about you in the past.

37:03.722 --> 37:06.292
I've had dreams about
entire cheerleading squads,

37:06.325 --> 37:08.360
so don't get me wrong.

37:08.394 --> 37:10.562
It's kid stuff, you know.
How 'bout you?

37:10.596 --> 37:11.930
Do I dream?
Mmm.

37:14.466 --> 37:16.368
That's about all I do.

37:30.382 --> 37:33.785
ROGER:
Raisin' a kid's hard work.
You got any kids?

37:33.819 --> 37:36.688
No, sir. No, sir.
And from
listening to you talking

37:36.722 --> 37:38.590
and from observin' this,

37:38.624 --> 37:41.760
I'm kinda grateful old Emily
turned up infertile.

37:58.944 --> 38:01.747
Shouldn't you be
cleaning up the store?

38:02.648 --> 38:04.015
I got plenty of time.

38:04.716 --> 38:06.685
Big store.
Huge.

38:08.654 --> 38:09.988
Always smoke cigars?

38:11.690 --> 38:13.959
I enjoy a good one
after a fine meal.

38:13.992 --> 38:15.927
It settles the stomach.

38:17.128 --> 38:18.797
You're the town liar, right?

38:23.769 --> 38:24.870
What?

38:24.903 --> 38:28.907
I'm sorry.
That really came out wrong.

38:28.940 --> 38:30.642
I don't see how
something like that
could come out right.

38:30.676 --> 38:32.010
I guess I meant that's
what people call you.

38:32.043 --> 38:33.512
But I didn't mean to imply
that it's actually true.

38:33.545 --> 38:34.680
People are
actually calling me that?

38:34.713 --> 38:36.382
I thought you knew.

38:36.415 --> 38:37.783
Know what?
That I was the town liar?

38:37.816 --> 38:38.984
You didn't?

38:39.017 --> 38:40.051
No. I'm not.

38:40.085 --> 38:41.920
I think that you might have
the wrong information.

38:41.953 --> 38:43.054
I didn't mean to offend you.

38:44.523 --> 38:45.857
Did you think that
was a compliment?

38:45.891 --> 38:47.993
No. No. And I apologize.

38:48.026 --> 38:50.696
You know, I can't
repeat things like that.

38:50.729 --> 38:53.365
Don't think about it.
It's all right.

38:53.399 --> 38:55.834
As I said, I think you've got
the wrong information.

38:55.867 --> 38:57.836
But, if people
are calling me that,

38:57.869 --> 39:00.539
it's only
because they're small,
cheap, petty, and jealous.

39:00.572 --> 39:02.941
Small towns are notorious
for that kinda thing.

39:02.974 --> 39:04.142
I'm sure
there's a word for me.

39:04.175 --> 39:05.677
Oh, yeah. Sure.

39:05.711 --> 39:06.845
What do they call me?

39:06.878 --> 39:08.046
A tease.

39:08.079 --> 39:09.548
Tease?

39:11.483 --> 39:13.785
Yeah, I can see that.

39:13.819 --> 39:15.086
Mmm-hmm. Mmm-hmm.

39:15.120 --> 39:17.789
Actually, I never teased.

39:17.823 --> 39:20.058
This is becoming amusing.

39:20.091 --> 39:21.960
Who exactly calls me a liar?

39:21.993 --> 39:23.862
Everybody.

39:23.895 --> 39:25.564
Everybody.
No, not everybody.

39:25.597 --> 39:26.965
I'm sure there's
some old people in town.

39:26.998 --> 39:28.500
Right.

39:34.773 --> 39:36.508
Well, what do you think?

39:36.542 --> 39:38.009
What do I think?

39:40.011 --> 39:41.880
Do you think I'm a liar?

39:41.913 --> 39:44.015
Well,
I don't know you well enough.

39:45.851 --> 39:47.819
You've known me
for almost 17 years.

39:47.853 --> 39:50.121
We went to the same schools
from kindergarten on up.

39:50.155 --> 39:52.891
I knew of you,
but I didn't
know you personally.

39:54.460 --> 39:56.194
That's always bothered me.

39:56.227 --> 39:59.931
I mean, that old "in-out,
us-them" thing.

39:59.965 --> 40:01.500
That's the way it's been.

40:01.533 --> 40:02.834
I know.
It's always bothered me.

40:02.868 --> 40:05.170
Sure, but it's
water over the dam now.

40:05.203 --> 40:08.607
(SIGHS) Yeah, but it's
your dam and my water.

40:08.640 --> 40:10.442
I got crapped on
a lot of years.

40:10.476 --> 40:12.611
I just meant that
it's in the past.

40:12.644 --> 40:15.481
Well, the present is
a result of the past.

40:15.514 --> 40:17.683
I look at my high
school yearbook,

40:17.716 --> 40:20.752
and I don't see
four fabulous years.

40:20.786 --> 40:22.921
Actually, what I'm reminded of
is what it feels like

40:22.954 --> 40:25.023
to have my
underwear yanked up my ass

40:25.056 --> 40:27.526
by some big football player
with arms like
telephone poles.

40:27.559 --> 40:29.928
Okay,
and where are those guys now?

40:31.663 --> 40:36.067
I know they're not
working nights at Target.
I'll tell you that. (LAUGHS)

40:36.101 --> 40:38.904
(CHUCKLES) Yeah. You know,

40:38.937 --> 40:40.906
I look at my yearbook

40:40.939 --> 40:44.142
and I see four fabulous years

40:45.777 --> 40:47.679
that are gonna be
the highlight of my life.

40:47.713 --> 40:49.781
Here's what it's like...

40:49.815 --> 40:53.018
First,
you feel a hand going down
the back of your pants

40:53.051 --> 40:54.786
and tighten around
the elastic waistband...

40:54.820 --> 40:56.522
Highlight.

40:56.555 --> 40:58.189
Sometimes I'd
actually see stars.

